**1. Workflow Overview**

The ELECTRON-2 Content Generator is the core content production pipeline
for the CorpFit QUANTUM AI Content Factory. It takes a production brief
(topic, platform, module, funnel, duration), retrieves relevant brand
rules and banned phrases from the Qdrant vector database, assembles a
hybrid prompt (static core + dynamic knowledge), sends it to Claude
Sonnet 4, parses the structured output, performs dual-layer safety
scanning, stores the result in PostgreSQL, and handles errors with retry
logic.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Parse Brief \> Qdrant Brand Rules \> Qdrant Banned Phrases \>
  Assemble Prompt \> Claude API \> Parse Output \> Banned Phrase Check \>
  Store Result \> Error Handler**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**1.1 Workflow Evolution**

  -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Version**   **Day**   **Nodes**   **Architecture**
  ------------- --------- ----------- -------------------------------------------
  v1            Day 3     2           Manual Trigger → HTTP Request (hardcoded
                                      3,300-word prompt)

  v2            Day 4     6           \+ Parse Brief, Qdrant Brand Rules, Qdrant
                                      Banned Phrases, Assemble Prompt, Code Node
                                      API

  v3            Day 5     8           \+ Parse Output (structured JSON) + Banned
                                      Phrase Check (dual-layer safety)

  **v4**        **Day 6** **10**      **+ Store Result (PostgreSQL) + Error
                                      Handler (retry logic + graceful fallback)**
  -------------------------------------------------------------------------------

**1.2 Key Concept: Hybrid RAG Approach**

The workflow uses a hybrid approach with two distinct prompt layers:

+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| **STATIC CORE (\~1,200 words)**   | **DYNAMIC KNOWLEDGE (from         |
|                                   | Qdrant)**                         |
| Hardcoded in Assemble Prompt      |                                   |
| node. Defines WHO the agent is    | Pulled at runtime from Qdrant     |
| and HOW it works. Never changes.  | vector DB. Tells WHAT to follow.  |
|                                   | Changes and grows over time.      |
| • Agent identity (ELECTRON-2)     |                                   |
|                                   | • Brand colors, fonts, visual     |
| • Output format with emoji        | guidelines                        |
| headers                           |                                   |
|                                   | • Platform-specific tone rules    |
| • Workflow steps (Parse \> Plan   |                                   |
| \> Create \> Check)               | • Module definitions (5 modules)  |
|                                   |                                   |
| • Safe framing rules              | • 71 banned phrases               |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **ANALOGY**                                                           |
|                                                                       |
| The static core is like a chef\'s training and cooking technique      |
| (doesn\'t change). The dynamic knowledge is like today\'s menu and    |
| ingredient restrictions (changes regularly). You don\'t retrain the   |
| chef every time you add a new dish --- you just update the menu.      |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

