**3. Node-by-Node Specification**

Each node is detailed below with its purpose, inputs, outputs, and
technical implementation notes.

  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------
  **NODE 1: MANUAL 
  TRIGGER**        

  **Type**         Trigger Node (n8n built-in)

  **Added**        Day 3

  **Purpose**      Starts the pipeline execution. Currently activated by
                   clicking \'Test Workflow\' in n8n. Will be replaced by
                   QUANTUM webhook/cron trigger in Phase 3 (Day 7).

  **Input**        None (user click)

  **Output**       Empty item → triggers Node 2
  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------

**Future upgrade:** This trigger will be replaced with either a QUANTUM
orchestrator webhook (for on-demand generation) or a cron schedule (for
automated daily/weekly content batches). The QUANTUM system will pass
the brief directly into the trigger, eliminating manual input.

  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------
  **NODE 2: PARSE  
  BRIEF**          

  **Type**         Set Node (n8n built-in)

  **Added**        Day 4

  **Purpose**      Extracts and structures the production brief into 5
                   clean fields that all downstream nodes can reference.

  **Input**        Raw brief parameters (manually configured in node)

  **Output**       1 structured item with 5 fields: module, platform,
                   funnel, topic, duration
  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------

**Brief Fields**

  ------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Field**   **Example Value**     **Description**
  ----------- --------------------- --------------------------------------
  module      Steps                 One of 5 CorpFit modules (Steps,
                                    Workouts, Meals, Check-in, Events)

  platform    TikTok                Target social platform (TikTok,
                                    Instagram, LinkedIn)

  funnel      B2C                   Audience funnel (B2B for corporate HR,
                                    B2C for individual users)

  topic       Desk stretches for    Specific content topic
              office workers        

  duration    30s                   Target video duration
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Design decision:** Using a Set node (not a Code node) keeps brief
parsing simple and visual. Anyone can click the node in n8n and
immediately see/edit all 5 fields without reading JavaScript.

  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------
  **NODE 3:        
  CORPFIT QDRANT** 

  **Type**         Vector Store (Qdrant)

  **Added**        Day 4

  **Purpose**      Performs semantic search against the
                   corpfit_brand_rules collection in Qdrant to retrieve
                   the 15 most relevant brand rules for the current
                   content brief.

  **Input**        Brief fields (module, platform, funnel) from Node 2

  **Output**       15 brand rule items (text + relevance score)
  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------

**How Semantic Search Works**

The node converts the brief\'s topic and platform into a vector
embedding using Ollama\'s nomic-embed-text model, then finds the 15
closest matching rules in the Qdrant collection. This means a
TikTok/Steps brief automatically pulls TikTok tone rules and Steps
module definitions, while a LinkedIn/Events brief pulls LinkedIn
professionalism rules and Events guidelines.

**Collection Details**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Property**           **Value**
  ---------------------- ------------------------------------------------
  Collection             corpfit_brand_rules

  Total Entries          44

  Retrieval Limit        15 per query

  Embedding Model        nomic-embed-text (via Ollama at ollama:11434)

  Vector Size            768 dimensions

  Distance Metric        Cosine similarity
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**Why 15 items?** Testing showed 15 provides the right balance: enough
context for Claude to apply brand rules accurately, but not so many that
irrelevant rules dilute the prompt. Increasing to 20+ added noise
without improving output quality.

  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------
  **NODE 4: GET    
  BANNED PHRASES** 

  **Type**         Vector Store (Qdrant)

  **Added**        Day 4

  **Purpose**      Loads ALL banned phrases from the
                   corpfit_banned_phrases collection. Unlike Node 3
                   (which does smart retrieval), this node loads the
                   complete safety net --- every single phrase that
                   ELECTRON-2 must never use.

  **Input**        Brief fields from Node 2 (used as search query)

  **Output**       All 71 banned phrase items
  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------

**Collection Details**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Property**           **Value**
  ---------------------- ------------------------------------------------
  Collection             corpfit_banned_phrases

  Total Entries          71

  Retrieval Limit        75 (headroom above 71 entries)

  Embedding Model        nomic-embed-text (via Ollama at ollama:11434)
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**Banned Phrase Categories**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Category**     **Examples**                          **Count**
  ---------------- ------------------------------------- ----------------
  Health Claims    \"cure\", \"treat\", \"heal\",        \~20
                   \"fix\", \"guarantee results\"        

  Diet Culture     \"cheat meal\", \"guilty pleasure\",  \~15
                   \"no pain no gain\"                   

  Body Shaming     \"beach body\", \"bikini body\",      \~12
                   \"skinny\"                            

  Medical Terms    \"prescription\", \"diagnosis\",      \~10
                   \"therapy\"                           

  Competitor Refs  \"FunFit\", \"competitor names\"      \~8

  Absolute         \"always\", \"never\", \"everyone     \~6
  Language         should\"                              
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**Why load ALL?** Banned phrases are a safety net, not a relevance
query. Missing even one dangerous phrase (like \'cures diabetes\') could
cause real harm. The full list at 71 entries adds minimal tokens (\~500)
to the prompt --- a worthwhile trade-off for complete safety coverage.

  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------
  **NODE 5:        
  ASSEMBLE         
  PROMPT**         

  **Type**         Code Node (JavaScript)

  **Added**        Day 4

  **Purpose**      The brain of the pipeline. Merges the static core
                   prompt (\~1,200 words), the 15 dynamically retrieved
                   brand rules, and all 71 banned phrases into one
                   complete system prompt for Claude.

  **Input**        Brief (Node 2) + Brand Rules (Node 3) + Banned Phrases
                   (Node 4)

  **Output**       1 item containing: assembled system prompt + user
                   message (brief)
  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------

**Prompt Assembly Logic**

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| // Pseudocode for prompt assembly                                     |
|                                                                       |
| const systemPrompt = \[                                               |
|                                                                       |
| STATIC_CORE, // \~1,200 words (hardcoded)                             |
|                                                                       |
| \"\\n\-\-- BRAND RULES \-\--\\n\",                                    |
|                                                                       |
| brandRules.map(r =\> // 15 items from Qdrant                          |
|                                                                       |
| r.text).join(\"\\n\"),                                                |
|                                                                       |
| \"\\n\-\-- BANNED PHRASES \-\--\\n\",                                 |
|                                                                       |
| bannedPhrases.map(p =\> // 71 items from Qdrant                       |
|                                                                       |
| p.text).join(\", \")                                                  |
|                                                                       |
| \].join(\"\\n\");                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| const userMessage =                                                   |
|                                                                       |
| \`Create content for: \${topic}                                       |
|                                                                       |
| Platform: \${platform} \| Module: \${module}                          |
|                                                                       |
| Funnel: \${funnel} \| Duration: \${duration}\`;                       |
|                                                                       |
| return { systemPrompt, userMessage };                                 |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**Token Breakdown (Estimated)**

  ------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Component**              **Tokens**             **% of Total**
  -------------------------- ---------------------- ----------------------
  Static Core                \~800                  40%

  Brand Rules (15 items)     \~600                  30%

  Banned Phrases (71 items)  \~400                  20%

  Brief / User Message       \~200                  10%

  TOTAL INPUT                \~2,000                100%
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------

  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------
  **NODE 6: CALL   
  CLAUDE API**     

  **Type**         Code Node (JavaScript)

  **Added**        Day 4

  **Purpose**      Sends the assembled prompt to Claude Sonnet 4 via the
                   Anthropic API and receives the complete content
                   package as raw text.

  **Input**        Assembled system prompt + user message from Node 5

  **Output**       1 item containing Claude\'s raw text response
                   (\~1,500-2,500 words)
  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------

**API Configuration**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Parameter**          **Value**
  ---------------------- ------------------------------------------------
  Endpoint               https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages

  Model                  claude-sonnet-4-20250514

  Max Tokens             4096

  Temperature            0.7 (balanced creativity + consistency)

  API Key                Stored in n8n credentials (corpfit-quantum)

  HTTP Method            this.helpers.httpRequest() (n8n sandboxed)
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**Why this.helpers.httpRequest()?**

n8n Code nodes run in a sandboxed JavaScript environment where standard
fetch() and \$http methods are not available. After 5 failed debugging
attempts with HTTP Request nodes and other methods,
this.helpers.httpRequest() was discovered as the correct approach ---
it\'s n8n\'s native sandboxed HTTP client that bypasses all body/header
parsing conflicts.

**Cost Per Generation**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Metric**                 **Value**
  -------------------------- --------------------------------------------
  Input tokens               \~2,000 (\$0.003 per 1K = \$0.006)

  Output tokens              \~1,500 (\$0.015 per 1K = \$0.0225)

  Total per piece            \~\$0.005 (after accounting for caching)

  Monthly (72 pieces)        \~\$0.36
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------
  **NODE 7: PARSE  
  OUTPUT**         

  **Type**         Code Node (JavaScript)

  **Added**        Day 5

  **Purpose**      Extracts 10 structured content fields from Claude\'s
                   raw text response. Converts one giant text blob into
                   clean, individually accessible JSON fields.

  **Input**        Raw text response from Node 6

  **Output**       1 item with 10 structured JSON fields
  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------

**Extracted Fields**

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **\#**   **Field**        **Description**             **Example**
  -------- ---------------- --------------------------- --------------------------
  1        brief_summary    One-line summary of the     30s TikTok for B2C: desk
                            content brief               stretches

  2        hooks            3 attention-grabbing        \"Your desk is slowly
                            opening lines               killing you\...\"

  3        script           Complete video script with  \[0-5s\] Hook \| \[5-20s\]
                            timestamps                  Demo \| \[20-30s\] CTA

  4        on_screen_text   Text overlays for the video \"Try this NOW\" \| \"3
                                                        stretches\"

  5        storyboard       Visual scene descriptions   Scene 1: Office worker at
                                                        desk\...

  6        caption_short    Short social media caption  Your desk routine needs
                                                        this 💪

  7        caption_long     Extended caption with       Full paragraph + #CorpFit
                            hashtags                    #WellnessAtWork

  8        cta              Call to action              Download CorpFit → link in
                                                        bio

  9        disclaimer       Health/safety disclaimer    Consult a healthcare
                                                        professional\...

  10       self_check       Agent\'s own compliance     UAF compliance: 10/10
                            report                      checks passed
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Parsing Method**

The parser uses emoji headers as section delimiters. Claude\'s output
follows the UAF-1.0 format with consistent emoji markers (e.g., 🎬 for
hooks, 📝 for script). The parser splits on these markers, trims
whitespace, and assigns each section to its corresponding JSON field.

  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------
  **NODE 8: BANNED 
  PHRASE CHECK**   

  **Type**         Code Node (JavaScript)

  **Added**        Day 5

  **Purpose**      The second safety layer. Scans every single content
                   field against all 71 banned phrases. This is the
                   automated post-generation safety gate that catches
                   anything Claude\'s built-in self-check might have
                   missed.

  **Input**        10 parsed content fields from Node 7 + banned phrases
                   list from Node 4

  **Output**       Original content + qa_passed (boolean) +
                   qa_violations_count + qa_violations (array)
  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------

**Dual-Layer Safety Architecture**

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Layer**   **Type**        **When**          **How**
  ----------- --------------- ----------------- -----------------------------
  Layer 1     Claude          During generation Built into UAF-1.0 prompt:
              Self-Check                        Claude checks its own output
                                                before responding

  Layer 2     Automated Scan  Post-generation   JavaScript loops through
                              (this node)       every field, checking against
                                                every banned phrase
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Scan Logic**

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| // Pseudocode for banned phrase scanning                              |
|                                                                       |
| const violations = \[\];                                              |
|                                                                       |
| const fields = \[hooks, script, caption_short, caption_long,          |
|                                                                       |
| cta, on_screen_text, storyboard, disclaimer,                          |
|                                                                       |
| brief_summary, self_check\];                                          |
|                                                                       |
| for (const field of fields) {                                         |
|                                                                       |
| for (const phrase of bannedPhrases) { // 71 phrases                   |
|                                                                       |
| if (field.toLowerCase().includes(phrase.toLowerCase())) {             |
|                                                                       |
| violations.push({ field: fieldName, phrase });                        |
|                                                                       |
| }                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| }                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| }                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| return {                                                              |
|                                                                       |
| \...contentFields,                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| qa_passed: violations.length === 0,                                   |
|                                                                       |
| qa_violations_count: violations.length,                               |
|                                                                       |
| qa_violations: violations,                                            |
|                                                                       |
| qa_status: violations.length === 0 ? \"CLEAN\" : \"FLAGGED\"          |
|                                                                       |
| };                                                                    |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**Track record:** Across all 10 tests, this node has detected 0 banned
phrase violations. Claude\'s Layer 1 self-check has been 100% effective
so far, but Layer 2 exists as an insurance policy --- no single point of
failure for content safety.

  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------
  **NODE 9: STORE  
  RESULT ✦ NEW Day 
  6**              

  **Type**         Code Node (JavaScript)

  **Added**        Day 6

  **Purpose**      Writes the complete content package (brief metadata,
                   all 10 content fields, QA results, system metadata,
                   and raw response) to the PostgreSQL content_logs table
                   for persistent storage, audit trails, and downstream
                   agent access.

  **Input**        All content fields + QA results from Node 8

  **Output**       Stored record ID + confirmation status
  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------

**Database Connection**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Parameter**          **Value**
  ---------------------- ------------------------------------------------
  Host (Docker)          postgres:5432

  Host (Browser)         localhost:5432

  Database               corpfit

  Table                  content_logs

  Total Columns          28

  Total Indexes          6
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**Schema: 28 Columns Across 6 Groups**

  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Group**       **Cols**   **Fields**
  --------------- ---------- -------------------------------------------------
  Identity        3          id (SERIAL PK), created_at (TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT
                             NOW()), updated_at

  Brief Metadata  5          module, platform, funnel, topic, duration

  Content Fields  10         brief_summary, hooks, script, on_screen_text,
                             storyboard, caption_short, caption_long, cta,
                             disclaimer, self_check

  QA Results      4          qa_passed (BOOLEAN), qa_violations_count (INT),
                             qa_violations (JSONB), qa_status (VARCHAR)

  System Metadata 4          model_used, pipeline_version,
                             token_count_estimate, generation_cost_usd

  Audit           2          raw_response (TEXT), approval_status (VARCHAR
                             DEFAULT \'pending\')
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Database Indexes**

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Index**                          **Purpose**
  ---------------------------------- ----------------------------------------
  idx_content_logs_created_at        Time-based queries and daily/weekly
                                     reporting

  idx_content_logs_module            Filter by content module (Steps,
                                     Workouts, Meals, Check-in, Events)

  idx_content_logs_platform          Filter by target platform (TikTok,
                                     Instagram, LinkedIn)

  idx_content_logs_funnel            Filter by B2B/B2C funnel

  idx_content_logs_qa_passed         Quick QA pass/fail filtering for QUANTUM
                                     review

  idx_content_logs_approval_status   Content approval pipeline tracking
                                     (pending/approved/blocked)
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------
  **NODE 10: ERROR 
  HANDLER ✦ NEW    
  Day 6**          

  **Type**         Code Node (JavaScript)

  **Added**        Day 6

  **Purpose**      Catches and manages errors from Claude API calls,
                   Qdrant queries, and PostgreSQL writes. Implements
                   retry logic with exponential backoff and graceful
                   fallbacks to prevent pipeline crashes.

  **Input**        Error outputs from Nodes 3, 4, 6, and 9

  **Output**       Error log entry + retry attempt or graceful fallback
  ---------------- ------------------------------------------------------

**Error Recovery Matrix**

  ------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Error Type**   **HTTP Code**   **Action**            **Fallback**
  ---------------- --------------- --------------------- -----------------
  Claude API       408 / 500 / 529 Retry 2x with backoff Mark job failed
  timeout                          (2s, 4s)              

  Claude API auth  401             Log and alert (no     Human review
  error                            retry)                

  Qdrant           Connection      Retry 1x              Use cached rules
  unreachable      refused                               

  PostgreSQL write Insert error    Retry 1x              Log to file
  fail                                                   

  Parse Output     Missing         Log raw response      Manual review
  failure          sections                              
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Retry Logic**

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| // Exponential backoff implementation                                 |
|                                                                       |
| async function retryWithBackoff(fn, maxRetries = 2) {                 |
|                                                                       |
| for (let attempt = 0; attempt \<= maxRetries; attempt++) {            |
|                                                                       |
| try {                                                                 |
|                                                                       |
| return await fn();                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| } catch (error) {                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| if (attempt === maxRetries) throw error;                              |
|                                                                       |
| const delay = Math.pow(2, attempt + 1) \* 1000; // 2s, 4s             |
|                                                                       |
| logError({                                                            |
|                                                                       |
| timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),                                  |
|                                                                       |
| node: error.node,                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| message: error.message,                                               |
|                                                                       |
| retryAttempt: attempt + 1,                                            |
|                                                                       |
| nextRetryIn: delay + \"ms\"                                           |
|                                                                       |
| });                                                                   |
|                                                                       |
| await sleep(delay);                                                   |
|                                                                       |
| }                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| }                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| }                                                                     |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**Error Monitoring**

All errors are logged with timestamp, originating node, error message,
and retry count. In Phase 3, QUANTUM will monitor these logs and can
trigger alerts when error rates exceed thresholds (e.g., 3+ failures in
1 hour).

